util

Class WeightedMultiHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.MultiMap<K,V>
      • util.WeightedMultiHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The key type.

    public final class WeightedMultiHashMap<K,V>
extends MultiMap<K,V>
    Extends the MultiHashMap with the ability to weight values.

    Adds functionality to permit random picking from the image of a key based on these weights. Each value in an image has its own separate weight. This means that the weight of (k1,v1) is not necessarily equal to the weight of (k2,v1). Values with unspecified weight are assumed to have a weight of 1. Values not in the mapping have a weight of 0.

    Author:
    Bitidork
